<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.1//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml11/DTD/xhtml11.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
 <head>
  <title>CSS Test: Adjustments to fit content to page must obey guidelines (letter-sized)</title>
  <link rel="author" title="Tom Clancy" href="mailto:tclancy@revenution.com"/>
  <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-page/#renderingpages"/>
  <meta name="flags" content="paged should" />
  <meta name="assert" content="The UA behaves reasonably when content is positioned outside the page box."/>
  <style type="text/css"><![CDATA[
   @page {
   	size:8.5in 11in;
	margin: 7%;
	padding: 2%;
	border: 4pt solid green;
   }
   p.offset {
		margin-left: 9in;
		border: 1pt solid aqua;
   }
  ]]></style>
 </head>
 <body>
	<p>When printed, only letter-sized (8.5&quot;x11in) paper should be available. This page must have a green border around all 4 sides. There may or may not be two boxes with blue borders appearing after this text. The user agent may consult the user before performing printing.</p>
